history.content:
Hi there, I'm not sure there is such a process. Presumably this new procedure was put in place to ensure students have a guaranteed 13 units. If you drop Theater, and do not get into 186, you're left below units and without a back-up plan. If the 186 waitlist isn't processing, it's for a valid reason. 

PS It looks like the combined enrollment of 186/286A is 481 which is the size of the lecture hall and the enrollment limit.  The only way to get the process to move more quickly would be for students currently enrolled to drop more quickly. You could share a message with the class piazza (if there is one) asking people who know they will eventually drop to do so now.

children.subject: That won't resolve OP's issue of having to drop some course after the drop deadline, which I believe is unresolvable.

I had a similar issue.. what I did was to switch sections using the "edit" option. this put me on the waitlist for the course I was trying to drop. once it was on my waitlist I was able to drop it.

I don't know if you can do the same for your course, but that's the "work-around" I found

history.content:
Here is my situation:

I am currently waitlisted as #2 for CS186, and enrolled in Theater 177. I am officially enrolled in 13 units (NOT including CS186). I wish to drop Theater 177 but I cannot because CalCentral says "You cannot drop this class. Dropping this class would put you below the minimum required units", I'm assuming because I would drop below 13 units if I were to drop this class. However, I think I will get into CS186 even though I'm still technically waitlisted.

The drop deadline without having to pay the $10 fee is this Friday, and it is taking a while for the CS186 waitlist to process...what would be the best way to request some sort of "speeding up" of the process before I have to pay $10 to drop a class that I want to drop but cannot through the system?
